<DocsLayout title="Quick Start">
  <h2>Quick Start Guide</h2>
  <p>
    Get up and running with Rep-li-bot in just a few minutes.
    This guide will walk you through your first app build.
  </p>

  <h3>1. Launch Rep-li-bot</h3>
  <p>
    Open Rep-li-bot from your Start menu or desktop shortcut.
    The app will display the launcher screen showing your existing projects.
  </p>

  <h3>2. Create a New Project</h3>
  <p>Click the "Create New" button to start the project wizard.</p>

  <h3>3. Describe Your App</h3>
  <p>
    In the builder screen, describe what you want in plain English.
    For example:
  </p>
  <pre><code>A simple expense tracker that lets me:
- Add expenses with amount, category, and date
- View a list of all expenses
- See total spending by category
- Export to CSV</code></pre>

  <h3>4. AI Generation</h3>
  <p>
    Click "Generate" and Rep-li-bot will use AI to create your app.
    The generation process includes validation and one repair pass if needed.
  </p>

  <h3>5. Preview & Run</h3>
  <p>
    Once generated, click "Preview" to see your app in the sandboxed preview harness.
    If everything looks good, click "Run" to launch it as a standalone window.
  </p>

  <h3>Tips for Better Results</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Be specific about inputs and outputs</li>
    <li>Mention any data structures you want (lists, tables, etc.)</li>
    <li>Describe the user flow step by step</li>
    <li>Include any specific features like export, search, or filtering</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Next Steps</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/docs/usage">Learn more about creating projects</a></li>
    <li><a href="/docs/themes">Customize with themes</a></li>
    <li><a href="/docs/ai-configuration">Configure AI settings</a></li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
